WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

00:51.217 --> 00:52.469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

00:52.552 --> 00:53.970
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:54.054 --> 00:54.971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

01:18.787 --> 01:19.954
Na-hyun.

01:22.373 --> 01:23.374
Han Na-hyun!

01:25.043 --> 01:26.711
What do you want?

01:26.795 --> 01:27.879
Mom!

01:28.421 --> 01:30.256
Didn't you say you were going to study?

01:30.882 --> 01:33.635
Where's the Na-hyun that was
too busy studying to run an errand for me?

01:33.718 --> 01:35.595
Mom, let me explain.

01:37.514 --> 01:39.140
I really was studying.

01:39.682 --> 01:41.768
I was. I really was.

01:41.851 --> 01:43.353
I knew you'd get caught.

01:44.062 --> 01:46.481
You should've given me a heads-up!

01:46.564 --> 01:48.983
Why is that my fault?

01:49.067 --> 01:51.027
Quiet down, both of you.

01:51.111 --> 01:52.695
-She started it.
-She started it.

01:52.779 --> 01:54.656
Are you going to keep bickering like this?

01:54.739 --> 01:56.074
Even when you're old and gray?

02:05.875 --> 02:09.379
HAN NA-HYUN, HAN SO-HYUN

02:16.845 --> 02:18.972
AUGUST 20, 1997
IT RAINED SO I WORE MY RAINCOAT…

02:26.521 --> 02:27.522
AUGUST 12, 2008

02:31.985 --> 02:33.278
My dear So-hyun

02:34.404 --> 02:35.947
hasn't grown old at all.

02:37.157 --> 02:39.868
HIGH SCHOOL GIRL JUMPS IN
AT THE MOMENT OF CRISIS

02:53.256 --> 02:54.257
Wow.

02:55.258 --> 02:56.759
The stars are beautiful.

03:04.058 --> 03:05.268
They really came.

03:19.240 --> 03:21.200
Excuse me. Are you…

03:29.584 --> 03:31.836
HAN SO-HYUN'S 19TH BIRTHDAY
ON JULY 7, 2012

03:44.349 --> 03:45.725
What's that?

03:49.187 --> 03:50.730
Those punks.

03:56.027 --> 03:57.070
Oh, no.

03:58.112 --> 04:00.073
This is not how I wanted it to start.

04:04.327 --> 04:05.870
You annoying bastard.

04:06.371 --> 04:09.707
You're just dying
for a good beating, aren't you?

04:10.541 --> 04:11.709
That's enough!

04:15.880 --> 04:17.048
What the hell does he want?

04:17.548 --> 04:21.594
Three ganging up on one?
Hey, that's cheap.

04:22.595 --> 04:24.222
If you're drunk, keep on walking.

04:25.265 --> 04:28.726
You won't be able to hold a spoon if
your last good hand is in a cast, mister.

04:29.644 --> 04:30.770
Mister?

04:31.813 --> 04:33.731
What the heck are you saying?

04:33.815 --> 04:35.525
Looks like this guy won't listen.

04:36.234 --> 04:37.443
A beating might do.

04:59.048 --> 05:02.302
HORANG TAEKWONDO
CERTIFICATE OF COMMENDATION

05:05.722 --> 05:08.057
You can't do this, sir.

05:08.141 --> 05:10.018
Or is this because I'm young?

05:11.894 --> 05:13.146
You do look young for your age.

05:15.356 --> 05:17.650
Those boys were ganging up on the kid!

05:17.734 --> 05:19.736
Keep your voice down.
You're in a police station.

05:19.819 --> 05:20.987
-Have a good one.
-You too.

05:21.612 --> 05:24.198
Officer! Wait!

05:24.282 --> 05:25.283
Shut up!

05:28.911 --> 05:30.663
Shut your mouth, okay?

05:31.289 --> 05:34.334
I can't sleep because of you.

05:36.169 --> 05:37.170
Not again.

05:37.920 --> 05:39.881
This is nuts!

05:41.507 --> 05:42.508
You're here too.

05:43.217 --> 05:44.510
This is actually good.

05:44.594 --> 05:47.180
You saw them beat up a boy, right?

05:47.764 --> 05:48.765
I did.

05:49.557 --> 05:53.978
Did you really fight
those three teenage boys alone?

05:57.815 --> 06:01.527
Fortunately, I practiced tae kwon do
since I was little.

06:03.029 --> 06:06.240
Did you perhaps get those men in here too?

06:06.324 --> 06:08.326
Is he crazy? He's talking to himself.

06:09.160 --> 06:12.789
Yes, I got them all in here
because they broke the law.

06:13.331 --> 06:14.791
You break the law, you get punished.

06:16.459 --> 06:19.003
You don't know when to gloss over things.

06:20.088 --> 06:22.090
You shouldn't gloss things over!

06:22.173 --> 06:24.300
If you make compromises and cut corners,

06:24.383 --> 06:27.720
the world would become a total mess
in an instant, mister.

06:28.346 --> 06:31.933
You see, my goal is
to make a fair and beautiful world

06:32.016 --> 06:34.894
where social order is maintained
by the law

06:35.520 --> 06:39.148
and people respect each other.

06:40.441 --> 06:43.069
That's why you wanted to be an attorney.

06:43.152 --> 06:47.031
For that to happen, I shouldn't be easy
even on minor misconduct.

06:50.660 --> 06:51.911
Anyway,

06:51.994 --> 06:53.955
why do you speak to me so formally?

06:54.038 --> 06:55.498
I'm a whole lot younger than you.

06:55.581 --> 06:58.543
You're Attorney Han's older sister.

06:59.502 --> 07:00.628
What?

07:00.711 --> 07:02.880
I mean…

07:05.842 --> 07:08.511
Okay, I'll be more casual with you.

07:09.345 --> 07:10.346
Of course.

07:11.931 --> 07:15.309
Anyway, I didn't mean
to get you locked up in here too.

07:16.018 --> 07:17.270
I'm sorry.

07:19.689 --> 07:23.985
Later when the officer comes,
I'll talk him into releasing you.

07:24.068 --> 07:27.405
You don't have to wait.
You can get out of here if you want.

07:28.322 --> 07:30.450
What? How?

07:31.284 --> 07:32.618
I'm behind steel bars…

07:37.707 --> 07:42.879
<i>Five fish altogether in one fish tank</i>

07:47.508 --> 07:48.509
Hello?

07:49.135 --> 07:51.053
<i>Is this Mr. Shin I-rang's brother-in-law?</i>

07:51.137 --> 07:52.930
Yes, this is me. Who may you be?

07:53.014 --> 07:55.308
I'm Lieutenant Cho Chi-yeong
from Seocho Police Station.

07:56.309 --> 07:57.685
Police?

07:58.644 --> 08:01.147
Have you settled down now?

08:02.648 --> 08:04.775
No, I'm boiling with anger.

08:05.485 --> 08:07.487
I'm so young! Why did I die?

08:08.779 --> 08:09.780
I know how you feel.

08:10.406 --> 08:11.699
You must be sad and frustrated.

08:11.782 --> 08:14.911
What's worse is
that I can't remember a thing.

08:15.912 --> 08:17.288
You don't?

08:18.080 --> 08:20.041
-That's strange.
-What do you mean?

08:20.124 --> 08:23.794
Ghosts float in mid-air
until they regain their memory.

08:23.878 --> 08:26.130
But you're already on the ground.

08:27.256 --> 08:31.010
Anyway, I can help you regain your memory.

08:31.093 --> 08:32.094
How?

08:32.720 --> 08:35.932
If I tell you your name
and date of birth--

08:36.015 --> 08:38.017
Tell me quick.

08:38.726 --> 08:39.936
Your memory will come back.

08:40.019 --> 08:41.604
Make it come back right now!

08:42.188 --> 08:43.564
Okay, all right.

08:43.648 --> 08:46.234
First, take a deep breath.

08:51.239 --> 08:53.616
-Come on, mister!
-All right.

08:53.699 --> 08:56.452
You've got a temper just like your sister.

08:59.956 --> 09:02.083
HAN SO-HYUN'S 19TH BIRTHDAY
ON JULY 7, 2012

09:06.087 --> 09:07.088
Han So-hyun.

09:13.511 --> 09:17.723
You were born on July 7, 1994.

09:26.649 --> 09:27.692
HAN SO-HYUN

09:27.775 --> 09:29.235
Sister.

09:31.028 --> 09:32.363
HORANG TAEKWONDO

09:34.365 --> 09:36.158
Hey! Get your hands off her!

09:40.246 --> 09:41.372
It's going to be real fun.

09:41.455 --> 09:42.832
Na-hyun!

09:49.630 --> 09:50.715
So-hyun!

10:05.313 --> 10:06.355
Na-hyun…

10:13.154 --> 10:14.196
I…

10:20.077 --> 10:21.662
I saved her.

10:25.333 --> 10:27.627
I saved my sister, Na-hyun.

10:31.130 --> 10:32.214
I see.

10:35.968 --> 10:38.387
I'm dead, but I'm happy.

10:41.015 --> 10:42.099
Mister.

10:43.559 --> 10:44.769
My sister

10:46.020 --> 10:48.272
must be well and happy, right?

10:52.652 --> 10:54.528
Oh, my head…

10:58.949 --> 11:01.202
How much did I drink?

11:11.212 --> 11:13.339
What is Attorney Shin's jacket doing here?

11:23.057 --> 11:24.183
Hello?

11:24.266 --> 11:26.477
<i>Attorney Han,</i>
<i>please help my brother-in-law!</i>

11:27.812 --> 11:28.813
Excuse me?

11:31.232 --> 11:33.067
What year is it now?

11:34.485 --> 11:36.195
It's 2025.

11:38.447 --> 11:40.074
Then,

11:41.283 --> 11:42.576
thirty one…

11:44.578 --> 11:45.955
I wonder if she became a singer.

11:47.289 --> 11:50.501
Oh, my sister's dream was to be a singer.

11:51.085 --> 11:52.920
She just loved singing.

11:53.003 --> 11:55.881
She'd sing and play the guitar all day.

11:57.425 --> 11:58.717
Look.

11:59.677 --> 12:01.804
Your sister isn't a singer--

12:01.887 --> 12:04.223
Mr. Shin,
your attorney is here to see you.

12:11.939 --> 12:13.941
Attorney Han…

12:20.197 --> 12:21.198
Han Na-hyun?

12:25.286 --> 12:26.579
Is it really you?

12:28.497 --> 12:31.041
What the… You became an attorney?

12:32.293 --> 12:33.294
But why?

12:36.630 --> 12:39.341
Wow, it's amazing.

12:40.801 --> 12:42.678
The tiny little girl

12:43.512 --> 12:45.890
turned into this awesome career woman.

12:49.560 --> 12:51.145
Is this how you actually are?

12:54.732 --> 12:57.276
I want you to take this first.

12:58.444 --> 12:59.945
I'm not thirsty.

13:00.529 --> 13:02.573
Don't be so cold to him.

13:03.157 --> 13:05.201
I'm not asking you to drink it.

13:05.910 --> 13:09.121
If I act strange in any way,

13:09.205 --> 13:11.081
splash that water on me.

13:11.165 --> 13:12.500
Why should I?

13:13.209 --> 13:15.294
I'm not like you. I don't use violence.

13:15.377 --> 13:17.213
Yes, I know.

13:18.047 --> 13:19.590
Still, keep it with you.

13:20.132 --> 13:24.136
I'd appreciate it if you could splash
that on me, in case I act weird.

13:24.220 --> 13:26.805
You're doing me a favor.

13:26.889 --> 13:28.474
That's not violence, right?

13:35.147 --> 13:37.107
How are the boys?

13:37.691 --> 13:39.985
They'll take two, two,
and four weeks to heal.

13:40.569 --> 13:42.571
Do you usually have bad drinking habits?

13:43.489 --> 13:45.824
How could you use violence
against students?

13:45.908 --> 13:48.994
Na-hyun, that's not his fault.

13:49.078 --> 13:50.246
I have nothing to say.

13:50.329 --> 13:51.580
You better not.

13:52.748 --> 13:56.126
I wouldn't have taken on this case
if not for your brother-in-law.

13:58.170 --> 14:01.674
And I'm partly at fault
for drinking with you.

14:01.757 --> 14:04.301
Thank you for choosing to be my attorney.

14:05.678 --> 14:09.974
But three boys were ganging up on one kid.

14:10.891 --> 14:12.184
I heard differently.

14:13.102 --> 14:15.312
The boys were just talking

14:15.980 --> 14:17.856
when you attacked them out of the blue.

14:20.359 --> 14:21.944
That's not true!

14:22.027 --> 14:24.655
I swear there were three bullying one.

14:24.738 --> 14:27.116
And they attacked me first.

14:29.034 --> 14:31.579
Three boys were bullying one,

14:31.662 --> 14:33.581
and they attacked me first.

14:33.664 --> 14:35.791
The four victims testified the same.

14:36.584 --> 14:40.129
If you keep denying it, it'll be taken
to both criminal and civil suits.

14:41.088 --> 14:44.717
If you don't settle with the parents
of Sung Min-jae with a four-week injury,

14:44.800 --> 14:46.594
you'll get a six-month sentence, minimum.

14:47.761 --> 14:49.430
Then, you'll lose your law license.

14:50.014 --> 14:53.517
Don't jump to conclusions so easily
without even looking into it.

14:55.561 --> 14:57.479
Don't you believe me?

14:57.563 --> 14:59.231
It's best to reach a settlement.

14:59.732 --> 15:02.735
Settle with them no matter what.

15:02.818 --> 15:04.403
Hey, you don't know anything!

15:06.155 --> 15:07.239
I'll try.

15:07.323 --> 15:08.908
Of course, you should.

15:11.493 --> 15:14.330
Fortunately, the arrest warrant
was dismissed.

15:14.413 --> 15:15.748
Go back home for now.

15:17.374 --> 15:18.959
What kind of attorney are you?

15:21.795 --> 15:25.549
An attorney is supposed to listen
to their client and side with them.

15:27.384 --> 15:28.802
Are you getting worked up at me?

15:28.886 --> 15:30.429
You shouldn't do this to your client!

15:30.512 --> 15:32.640
Are you really the Han Na-hyun I know?

15:33.390 --> 15:34.808
The Han Na-hyun you know?

15:35.684 --> 15:38.437
What do you even know about me?
Watch what you say.

15:38.520 --> 15:39.939
So much for a drunk who beats kids.

15:40.564 --> 15:42.983
Those punks deserved a beating!

15:43.067 --> 15:45.319
That's pretty low,
coming from an attorney.

15:45.402 --> 15:48.113
What made you become this inflexible?
You're darn annoying!

15:57.289 --> 15:58.374
Darn annoying?

16:22.523 --> 16:25.359
Did you say something to your sister?

16:26.026 --> 16:27.820
I said she was darn annoying.

16:28.529 --> 16:29.571
What?

16:30.864 --> 16:33.325
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

16:35.035 --> 16:37.037
But why is she so mean?

16:37.121 --> 16:40.541
I'd be mad at someone
who beat high schoolers too.

16:40.624 --> 16:41.875
No.

16:41.959 --> 16:45.212
She isn't one to get angry
without even listening.

16:45.295 --> 16:47.631
It's so weird
that she became an attorney too.

16:47.715 --> 16:50.384
Why don't you go after her
if you're that curious?

16:51.385 --> 16:52.386
What about you?

16:52.970 --> 16:55.347
The arrest warrant is dismissed,
so I'll be released soon.

16:55.973 --> 16:57.307
Go on now.

17:05.774 --> 17:09.361
-<i>Over this amazing blue sky</i>
-Oh, there she goes again.

17:09.445 --> 17:12.656
-<i>Riding on the flying magic carpet</i>
-<i>Magic carpet</i>

17:12.740 --> 17:14.950
-<i>In this amazing</i>
-<i>In this amazing</i>

17:15.034 --> 17:17.161
-Dad, focus on driving!
-<i>Blue world</i>

17:18.245 --> 17:19.955
You don't even listen to music now?

17:21.915 --> 17:23.333
DAD

17:28.172 --> 17:29.173
DAD

17:34.720 --> 17:36.555
What changed you so much?

17:41.226 --> 17:42.227
Wow.

17:43.479 --> 17:45.314
My neighborhood hasn't changed at all.

17:46.940 --> 17:48.067
That's a relief.

18:07.127 --> 18:08.128
Dad?

18:22.726 --> 18:25.187
He's got so much more gray hair.

18:27.731 --> 18:29.191
And wrinkles too.

18:36.615 --> 18:39.243
OFF-DUTY

18:44.081 --> 18:46.250
Still, it's so nice…

18:48.836 --> 18:50.045
to see you, Dad.

19:06.478 --> 19:08.814
Honey, I'm home.

19:14.444 --> 19:15.946
This cushion is still here.

19:16.613 --> 19:18.448
But the sofa is new.

19:19.283 --> 19:20.284
It's nice.

19:20.367 --> 19:22.744
Something smells delicious.

19:22.828 --> 19:24.705
Welcome home. You must be hungry.

19:24.788 --> 19:26.707
-Go wash your hands.
-Okay.

19:39.219 --> 19:40.387
Mom.

19:49.521 --> 19:50.689
Mom…

20:05.787 --> 20:06.997
Wow.

20:07.080 --> 20:09.666
Your braised tofu looks so good, Mom.

20:11.293 --> 20:13.795
That <i>doenjang</i> stew looks delicious too.

20:14.922 --> 20:16.757
There you go,
drinking straight soju again.

20:16.840 --> 20:18.967
I told you to eat as you drink.

20:19.051 --> 20:21.303
-Okay, fine.
-Here.

20:22.679 --> 20:25.224
Did you try calling Na-hyun?

20:25.307 --> 20:28.644
Yes, but she just wants to dine out.

20:29.728 --> 20:30.729
I see.

20:32.105 --> 20:33.106
What?

20:33.649 --> 20:35.651
Are you sad that you can't cook
for our daughter?

20:35.734 --> 20:37.569
No, it's not that.

20:39.446 --> 20:41.198
I'm wondering if we should move.

20:43.450 --> 20:45.410
I think she's avoiding this house.

20:45.494 --> 20:47.788
No way.

20:47.871 --> 20:49.373
She's extremely busy.

20:49.456 --> 20:52.584
We should be grateful
that she's even making time for us.

20:54.294 --> 20:55.837
-You think?
-Of course.

20:57.923 --> 21:01.176
Don't overthink it.

21:01.260 --> 21:02.886
And don't walk on eggshells around her.

21:03.845 --> 21:05.472
Look who's talking.

21:05.555 --> 21:06.848
Geez.

21:07.599 --> 21:09.726
Oh, the news must be on. What time is it?

21:10.602 --> 21:11.728
Gosh.

21:12.437 --> 21:14.606
Han Na-hyun doesn't like this house?

21:16.400 --> 21:19.653
And you walk on eggshells around her?

21:21.863 --> 21:22.864
Why?

21:24.950 --> 21:26.618
Just why?

21:28.120 --> 21:30.205
-On your 6:00.
-I know. I can hear it.

21:30.289 --> 21:31.290
He's moving.

21:31.373 --> 21:33.709
-I got him.
-Come on. He's fast.

21:33.792 --> 21:35.210
-He's one tap.
-Okay.

21:35.294 --> 21:37.170
-He's going down.
-Get him.

21:37.254 --> 21:39.131
-Four o'clock.
-Where is he?

21:39.214 --> 21:43.093
-Hold on. I'll help you.
-Dang.

21:43.176 --> 21:45.470
-Hello?
-Darn, I'm out of ammo.

21:46.680 --> 21:47.889
Gather up now.

21:47.973 --> 21:49.725
-Where are you?
-Wait. Geez.

21:49.808 --> 21:51.393
It must be nice to skip school,

21:52.102 --> 21:53.437
away from your homeroom teacher.

21:54.104 --> 21:55.188
Who are you?

21:55.272 --> 21:56.648
I'm Attorney Yang Do-kyung.

21:56.732 --> 21:59.443
Attorney? Doesn't that make us the boss?

21:59.526 --> 22:01.111
Yeah, of course.

22:02.112 --> 22:03.989
Mr. Attorney, we're busy right now.

22:04.072 --> 22:05.115
Crazy bastard.

22:05.782 --> 22:06.908
Visit us another time.

22:09.286 --> 22:13.915
On behalf of you busy boys,
your parents hired me themselves.

22:15.500 --> 22:19.212
They're quite angry
that their precious sons got beaten

22:19.713 --> 22:22.883
without knowing what you've done
to Jun-ho for the past year.

22:29.681 --> 22:31.224
What happened that day?

22:35.604 --> 22:37.647
We already told the police everything.

22:37.731 --> 22:42.152
We were just messing around
when that lunatic came and did this to us.

22:42.861 --> 22:44.946
-You're lying.
-No, it's true.

22:45.030 --> 22:46.531
Let me tell you something important.

22:47.657 --> 22:50.410
That bastard who beat you up
got an attorney.

22:50.494 --> 22:53.622
When it comes to relentlessness,
she's number one in this field.

22:54.498 --> 22:55.665
It'll take no time for her

22:56.750 --> 22:58.335
to find out what you've done.

23:02.839 --> 23:03.965
You must be Min-jae.

23:06.259 --> 23:08.386
Your father is
the Vice-minister of Health and Welfare.

23:09.012 --> 23:11.848
Ji-hyeok, your mother is
a professor of law at Hanguk University.

23:13.308 --> 23:17.229
Your parents will be put
in a tight spot if the truth gets out.

23:17.312 --> 23:18.563
They'll kill me.

23:22.651 --> 23:23.652
Right.

23:24.444 --> 23:27.155
So now, be honest with me
about everything.

23:28.240 --> 23:29.991
Only then, I can protect you.

23:31.076 --> 23:33.954
I honestly don't care
about school violence.

23:34.788 --> 23:36.081
What I want to know

23:36.164 --> 23:38.625
is that attorney who assaulted you.

23:39.835 --> 23:42.921
Didn't you find anything weird
about that bastard?

24:52.240 --> 24:53.575
FILES
PARKING

25:29.361 --> 25:31.029
My mom knows about it too?

25:31.112 --> 25:32.113
Oh…

25:33.198 --> 25:35.992
Well, she heard me talk
about the settlement money with Sa-rang…

25:36.826 --> 25:38.078
Even my sister?

25:40.956 --> 25:42.582
Things happened that way.

25:44.000 --> 25:46.836
Mother said she'd find a way
to get the money.

25:47.462 --> 25:51.883
As soon as she heard
you could lose your law license,

25:51.967 --> 25:54.094
she stormed out.

25:55.553 --> 25:57.555
Still, she was understanding
after finding out

25:57.639 --> 25:59.975
that you were possessed
by Attorney Han's sister.

26:00.058 --> 26:05.397
Your sister and I are trying every way
to get the money too, so don't worry.

26:08.900 --> 26:10.193
-Bong-su.
-Yes?

26:11.987 --> 26:13.071
I'm sorry.

26:13.697 --> 26:14.698
And thanks.

26:43.018 --> 26:44.019
I'm sorry.

26:46.146 --> 26:48.315
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

26:49.232 --> 26:51.860
You're in trouble because of me.

26:52.819 --> 26:55.572
And I've discovered
the uncomfortable truth.

26:56.614 --> 26:58.742
What do you mean?

27:00.869 --> 27:04.414
Something's off
between Na-hyun and my parents.

27:05.749 --> 27:08.460
My family wasn't rich,

27:08.960 --> 27:10.837
but we'd laugh and have fun.

27:10.920 --> 27:12.630
We had the most positive energy.

27:13.715 --> 27:16.634
Now, my parents
walk on eggshells around Na-hyun.

27:17.427 --> 27:19.220
Na-hyun is really off too.

27:21.556 --> 27:24.100
I wonder what happened.

27:24.684 --> 27:26.186
Something huge happened.

27:27.937 --> 27:31.358
They lost you, their precious family.

27:32.525 --> 27:34.319
They must've been devastated.

27:35.945 --> 27:36.946
Oh.

27:38.948 --> 27:42.577
Why would a family drift apart
during sad times?

27:42.660 --> 27:44.788
I wouldn't say they drifted apart.

27:46.456 --> 27:48.291
They're probably being considerate.

27:49.084 --> 27:50.085
Considerate?

27:52.212 --> 27:53.922
Some kinds of sadness

27:54.672 --> 27:58.802
are so powerful that they quickly spread
to people around you.

28:06.059 --> 28:09.062
STORY WHERE HAPPINESS GROWS

28:14.943 --> 28:17.237
<i>Worried that your sadness would spread,</i>

28:17.821 --> 28:19.864
<i>you keep hiding your feelings,</i>

28:20.573 --> 28:22.867
<i>watch how you speak or behave,</i>

28:24.035 --> 28:25.078
<i>and even</i>

28:25.995 --> 28:27.789
<i>make secrets.</i>

28:30.542 --> 28:33.169
Because you try not to hurt
those around you,

28:33.753 --> 28:36.464
you'd rather drift apart
from them little by little.

28:38.842 --> 28:42.679
I don't want my family
to live like this because of me.

28:45.890 --> 28:47.308
It's so sad.

28:50.687 --> 28:55.400
All the ghosts who visited me
had their sad stories.

28:56.067 --> 28:57.527
But they all worked out.

28:58.611 --> 29:00.530
Now that you've come,

29:00.613 --> 29:03.032
your family may be able
to open up to each other.

29:03.867 --> 29:06.870
I'll do my best to help you.

29:09.164 --> 29:10.165
Thank you.

29:13.543 --> 29:15.754
But your situation is more urgent.

29:16.504 --> 29:17.505
My situation?

29:18.089 --> 29:20.884
If your family loses your house
and business because of me,

29:20.967 --> 29:22.051
it'll kill me.

29:22.135 --> 29:23.511
Wait.

29:23.595 --> 29:25.096
Though I'm already dead.

29:26.347 --> 29:27.348
Anyway.

29:29.809 --> 29:30.810
You're

29:31.936 --> 29:32.937
quite sweet.

29:33.021 --> 29:35.523
I can't let go of anything
that feels wrong.

29:36.649 --> 29:39.152
What should we do to clear your name?

29:40.904 --> 29:43.406
If what you saw that day is true,

29:43.490 --> 29:47.827
there has to be a reason why Jun-ho acts
like he isn't a victim of school bullying.

29:48.411 --> 29:51.080
That… is what you need to find out.

29:51.831 --> 29:53.416
-What? Me?
-Yes.

29:54.125 --> 29:55.210
How?

29:56.669 --> 29:58.338
You're a ghost, you know.

30:18.107 --> 30:20.276
-Hello.
-Hello.

30:21.945 --> 30:22.946
Hello.

30:38.753 --> 30:41.047
I'm sorry, but I don't know.

31:00.441 --> 31:02.026
SUNG MIN-JAE

31:12.078 --> 31:14.330
-Hello--
-<i>What took you so long to pick up?</i>

31:16.457 --> 31:17.458
Sorry.

31:17.542 --> 31:19.002
Who did you meet today?

31:19.586 --> 31:20.837
I didn't meet anyone.

31:20.920 --> 31:22.922
If you get caught lying,
I'll kill you for real.

31:24.507 --> 31:25.758
I'm not lying.

31:29.512 --> 31:31.764
Come to Heaven and Earth
by 5:00 p.m. later today.

31:31.848 --> 31:33.099
Don't forget the money.

31:34.017 --> 31:35.226
Okay.

31:50.158 --> 31:52.368
Why are you doing this to me?

31:54.412 --> 31:55.496
What did I do…

31:56.497 --> 31:58.082
to deserve this?

32:07.884 --> 32:09.093
I'm going to kill them.

32:20.605 --> 32:21.731
Who is it?

32:25.902 --> 32:27.862
Hello, I'm Attorney Han Na-hyun.

32:27.946 --> 32:29.322
Attorney?

32:29.989 --> 32:31.699
Are you Jun-ho's mother?

32:32.825 --> 32:33.826
Yes.

32:34.577 --> 32:36.955
Did something happen with my son?

32:38.039 --> 32:39.749
Didn't he tell you anything?

32:40.833 --> 32:44.170
I don't get to see him often
because I work at night.

32:45.171 --> 32:46.881
Did he cause some kind of trouble?

32:46.965 --> 32:47.966
No.

32:48.466 --> 32:51.970
Your son is involved in a small case,
but he's not an assailant.

32:54.305 --> 32:57.642
Do you perhaps know where he may be?

33:05.108 --> 33:06.109
Jun-ho.

33:20.331 --> 33:23.251
I saw it that day.

33:24.127 --> 33:25.461
Those guys were bullying you.

33:26.045 --> 33:28.673
No, they're all my friends.

33:29.716 --> 33:31.926
-We were just messing around.
-They aren't…

33:33.052 --> 33:34.178
your friends.

33:34.846 --> 33:37.265
-You know that.
-I don't get what you're saying.

33:37.348 --> 33:38.850
-Jun-ho.
-I'm leaving.

33:39.434 --> 33:40.476
Hey, Seo Jun-ho!

33:45.690 --> 33:47.025
So what are you going to do?

33:47.817 --> 33:48.860
What?

33:48.943 --> 33:51.029
What's your plan?
Are you really going to kill them?

33:54.240 --> 33:55.408
Long ago,

33:56.409 --> 33:58.327
there was a guy like you
back in my school.

33:59.787 --> 34:01.956
He was harassed by school bullies,

34:02.874 --> 34:05.209
but his parents and teachers
were clueless,

34:05.293 --> 34:07.587
not to mention his classmates.

34:07.670 --> 34:08.880
So what?

34:08.963 --> 34:10.715
Why are you telling me this?

34:10.798 --> 34:13.217
Guess why those guys hang out in packs.

34:13.968 --> 34:15.178
Because they're cowards.

34:16.095 --> 34:17.930
So don't hide.

34:18.014 --> 34:20.308
Fight back when they come at you.

34:20.391 --> 34:22.393
No, I can't do that.

34:22.477 --> 34:25.354
Nothing is impossible.
Only if you make up your--

34:25.438 --> 34:26.981
I can't do it, okay?

34:27.607 --> 34:29.525
I can't!

34:36.949 --> 34:39.202
Don't tell me…

34:40.787 --> 34:42.789
Do they have something on you?

34:45.917 --> 34:46.918
I'm leaving.

34:47.752 --> 34:48.961
Is that it?

34:49.629 --> 34:50.630
What if I do?

34:51.589 --> 34:53.758
Does it give me the right to kill them?

34:56.260 --> 34:58.262
-Hello, Jun-ho.
-Jun-ho, hi!

34:58.346 --> 35:01.224
I'm going to take a super fun video
from now on.

35:01.307 --> 35:03.726
-Let go of me.
-Lights, ready?

35:03.810 --> 35:06.437
-Hey, lights.
-One moment.

35:06.521 --> 35:08.106
All ready now.

35:08.189 --> 35:10.399
This bastard looks awfully pretty today.

35:10.483 --> 35:13.444
-Stop.
-Stay still for a sec, Jun-ho.

35:14.028 --> 35:15.655
They blackmailed you with it.

35:17.115 --> 35:18.116
Yes.

35:19.117 --> 35:22.370
Those scumbags took a video of me naked.

35:36.717 --> 35:39.637
Still, you shouldn't do the same to them.

35:40.847 --> 35:42.849
The guy I mentioned earlier

35:42.932 --> 35:44.934
ended up in juvenile hall

35:45.810 --> 35:48.020
after hitting those bullies with a brick.

35:49.021 --> 35:53.276
No one was there to understand
why he had to attack them.

35:54.277 --> 35:55.778
Your case will be the same.

35:56.696 --> 35:58.698
You'll only suffer more.

35:59.949 --> 36:01.409
So please.

36:02.410 --> 36:04.620
Give me the knife.

36:05.746 --> 36:06.747
Now.

36:21.053 --> 36:22.722
No, don't go!

36:22.805 --> 36:24.432
Don't go to them!

36:34.692 --> 36:37.069
An assailant can't meet a victim.
You know that.

36:38.404 --> 36:41.449
You should've told me
about the situation sooner.

36:42.158 --> 36:43.201
Unbelievable.

36:43.910 --> 36:44.911
Sorry.

36:44.994 --> 36:47.371
Did Jun-ho tell you
where he's meeting up with the boys?

36:48.497 --> 36:50.958
Five o'clock at Heaven and Earth.

36:51.042 --> 36:53.127
That means we have enough time.

36:54.045 --> 36:55.504
Heaven and Earth, right?

37:01.761 --> 37:02.970
Come on, follow me.

37:07.016 --> 37:08.768
POLICE STATION

37:08.851 --> 37:11.646
But this is only
Jun-ho's side of the story.

37:12.688 --> 37:14.023
You're right,

37:14.607 --> 37:18.861
but his classmates and the owner
of his part-time workplace

37:18.945 --> 37:22.490
saw a suspicious sight of school violence.

37:22.573 --> 37:25.284
They also said they'd testify if needed.

37:25.952 --> 37:27.328
I'd really appreciate your help.

37:34.585 --> 37:36.420
Were they unable to help?

37:36.504 --> 37:39.048
It seems like someone has to die
before they take action.

37:41.300 --> 37:42.927
But we're running out of time.

37:43.010 --> 37:46.097
I better take Jun-ho's video away
from them myself.

37:47.181 --> 37:51.352
It's the only evidence to prove
that they've been bullying him,

37:51.435 --> 37:54.021
let alone the day of the case.

37:54.981 --> 37:56.482
Sounds good. Let's go right away.

37:56.565 --> 37:58.943
No, not with you.

37:59.026 --> 38:02.822
They know what you look like.
What if they recognize you and run off?

38:03.406 --> 38:06.158
But I can't let you go alone.

38:06.742 --> 38:08.661
I know you better than that.

38:09.287 --> 38:10.830
There's another reason, isn't there?

38:11.414 --> 38:12.748
Yes.

38:12.832 --> 38:15.751
He can get another knife anytime.

38:16.294 --> 38:18.796
Now that I know, I must stop him.

38:23.092 --> 38:25.803
He's a diligent kid that will be happy

38:25.886 --> 38:28.597
if he can just get over this hump.

38:28.681 --> 38:30.683
A boy's life is on the line here.

38:31.350 --> 38:32.810
I'm going to do something about it.

38:33.894 --> 38:35.896
Don't ever come
inside the Internet café, okay?

38:36.605 --> 38:37.606
Okay.

38:38.190 --> 38:41.110
I'll wait nearby and only stop Jun-ho.

38:41.193 --> 38:43.946
Instead, my brother-in-law
will be there to assist you.

39:38.584 --> 39:39.668
Welcome.

39:40.586 --> 39:43.297
-For two, please.
-You may sit anywhere that isn't taken.

39:43.381 --> 39:44.382
Okay.

39:44.465 --> 39:46.759
HEAVEN AND EARTH PC

39:47.593 --> 39:48.636
UNDER CONSTRUCTION

40:04.777 --> 40:07.029
-Excuse me, the power is out!
-What the heck?

40:07.113 --> 40:08.948
-What's going on?
-I was so close to winning.

40:09.031 --> 40:10.157
Mister.

40:10.241 --> 40:11.409
Just testing things.

40:12.743 --> 40:15.371
-What are you doing? Turn it back on!
-Turn the power back on!

40:15.454 --> 40:17.790
-We're terribly sorry!
-He's so high maintenance.

40:19.959 --> 40:22.169
ATTORNEY YANG DO-KYUNG

40:23.587 --> 40:24.755
What's up?

40:25.297 --> 40:26.799
<i>I have good news for you.</i>

40:27.383 --> 40:29.593
The parents are willing to settle.

40:30.219 --> 40:34.473
I told them they should never settle
with a piece of trash who beats kids.

40:35.057 --> 40:38.561
But an attorney has no power, you know.
I follow what my clients say.

40:39.437 --> 40:41.772
Check the settlement agreement.
I texted it to you just now.

40:44.608 --> 40:45.609
SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT

40:47.027 --> 40:48.696
TOTAL AMOUNT: 150,000,000 WON

40:51.073 --> 40:53.784
Do you actually believe
50 million per person makes sense?

40:53.868 --> 40:56.620
Then, does an attorney
beating high schoolers make sense?

40:57.997 --> 41:02.543
When someone intellectually and socially
accomplished fails to set an example,

41:02.626 --> 41:05.546
they must be held accountable.

41:06.797 --> 41:09.258
Discuss it wisely with the assailant,

41:09.800 --> 41:13.554
and come to Taebaek by 6:00 p.m.
if you don't want I-rang to go to jail.

41:30.279 --> 41:31.363
Hello?

41:31.447 --> 41:33.365
<i>Hello, Ms. Attorney.</i>

41:33.949 --> 41:36.994
The victims' attorney just called me.

41:37.077 --> 41:40.331
They want me to come to Taebaek's office
by 6:00 p.m. for a settlement.

41:40.998 --> 41:43.292
Taebaek called you too?

41:43.375 --> 41:44.543
Yes.

41:44.627 --> 41:46.462
<i>I get what they're trying to pull.</i>

41:47.004 --> 41:49.590
<i>They're demanding 150 million won</i>
<i>for settlement money.</i>

41:49.673 --> 41:51.509
They must've expected

41:51.592 --> 41:54.261
Attorney Shin wouldn't
easily agree to the big sum

41:54.345 --> 41:55.971
and gave you a call too.

41:58.766 --> 42:01.560
I understand.

42:02.394 --> 42:04.230
I'll be there on time.

42:04.813 --> 42:07.274
Could you give me a little bit of time?

42:07.942 --> 42:09.235
How much time?

42:11.028 --> 42:12.363
About an hour or two.

42:13.614 --> 42:16.075
It'll be past 6:00 by then.

42:19.203 --> 42:23.082
Let me think only about my son right now.

42:24.208 --> 42:27.878
I don't want him to suffer.

42:28.462 --> 42:31.340
I understand how you feel, but…

42:31.423 --> 42:32.675
<i>It's okay.</i>

42:33.217 --> 42:35.094
Thank you for your concern.

42:48.983 --> 42:51.527
I'd like you to stay away from me.

42:52.361 --> 42:53.487
I know from experience

42:53.571 --> 42:56.490
that it's better to stay away from ghosts
in dangerous situations.

42:59.743 --> 43:02.496
Should I be with Na-hyun, then?

43:04.248 --> 43:05.874
Sounds good.

43:09.003 --> 43:10.045
I'm gonna take a leak.

43:10.129 --> 43:11.839
-I'm going with.
-Me too.

43:12.548 --> 43:14.717
Hey, just go upstairs.

43:14.800 --> 43:16.260
Jun-ho might run off.

43:16.343 --> 43:18.178
-Wait upstairs.
-Make it quick.

43:32.276 --> 43:33.652
I MADE A GROUP CHAT
THANKS, BONG-SU

43:34.278 --> 43:35.487
<i>One is going in.</i>

43:35.571 --> 43:36.655
One's here.

43:42.411 --> 43:43.412
<i>It's him, right?</i>

43:44.204 --> 43:46.123
<i>Yes, but why is he alone?</i>

43:46.957 --> 43:48.626
<i>Let's stick to the plan.</i>

44:05.559 --> 44:06.769
Hey, kid.

44:06.852 --> 44:09.521
You shouldn't take my picture, gosh.

44:09.605 --> 44:12.524
You really can't without permission.
I have rights to my own image.

44:12.608 --> 44:14.151
Why would I take a picture of you?

44:14.234 --> 44:16.487
Sure, I understand.

44:16.570 --> 44:19.114
It's rare to run into a celebrity
in this kind of neighborhood.

44:19.198 --> 44:21.241
-Still--
-I'm lost for words.

44:21.325 --> 44:23.869
Mister, I don't know who you are.

44:23.952 --> 44:25.829
Wait. You're him, right?

44:26.455 --> 44:27.998
Yoon Bong-su.

44:28.082 --> 44:29.958
He's really famous. Don't you know him?

44:30.042 --> 44:31.043
This guy?

44:31.126 --> 44:33.921
Was it <i>Showboating Squid</i>?

44:34.004 --> 44:36.590
No, <i>Steamboating Squid</i>! Right?
I enjoyed watching that drama!

44:36.674 --> 44:39.760
-Oh, goodness. You watched it?
-I really liked it.

44:39.843 --> 44:41.720
Han Na-hyun, are you really an attorney?

44:41.804 --> 44:42.930
You're a real celeb?

44:43.722 --> 44:45.140
I'd be one too, then.

44:45.224 --> 44:47.476
Anyway, I didn't take a picture of you.

44:47.559 --> 44:51.188
Oh, my. My fans are so shy.

44:51.271 --> 44:54.441
It's okay!
You know what? You're lucky today.

44:54.525 --> 44:56.860
-I'll take a selfie with you. Don't worry.
-No, thanks.

44:56.944 --> 44:58.904
-I'll make you look good.
-Let me do it for you.

44:58.987 --> 44:59.988
Oh, thank you.

45:04.785 --> 45:07.371
What the… You still have that phone?

45:07.996 --> 45:09.957
The attorney told us
to throw away our phones.

45:10.958 --> 45:12.251
Did you guys do it?

45:12.835 --> 45:13.877
Of course.

45:14.461 --> 45:17.756
I got a new one with Seo-won right away.

45:17.840 --> 45:18.841
Score!

45:21.218 --> 45:22.344
It's too good to waste.

45:23.178 --> 45:25.180
I'll toss it after showing his mom.

45:26.098 --> 45:27.975
She deserves to see her son's video.

45:28.725 --> 45:29.726
Don't you think?

45:31.019 --> 45:33.522
You always have a point.

45:33.605 --> 45:36.191
-I wish we edited a little better.
-Let me see.

45:37.234 --> 45:39.027
A masterpiece is a masterpiece after all.

46:02.926 --> 46:05.429
-The video isn't here.
-That can't be.

46:05.512 --> 46:08.182
-Oh, no.
-What are you doing? Give it back.

46:08.265 --> 46:10.350
-She's looking for a camera app.
-Give it back to me.

46:10.434 --> 46:12.019
DID YOU FIND IT?

46:18.150 --> 46:19.693
-Hold on…
-It's my phone.

46:21.195 --> 46:22.654
Damn it.

46:23.947 --> 46:25.324
Min-jae, run!

46:26.867 --> 46:28.785
-You're that guy…
-What?

46:28.869 --> 46:30.412
Fuck! Guys, run!

46:32.456 --> 46:33.665
Ow.

46:33.749 --> 46:34.958
Hey, stop right there!

46:35.042 --> 46:36.210
I got it!

46:52.309 --> 46:53.644
Over there!

47:02.736 --> 47:03.737
Attorney Yang.

47:04.738 --> 47:06.573
I'll send the police there.

47:06.657 --> 47:08.742
Don't worry, and get out of there.

47:09.535 --> 47:11.787
You got a new phone,
so you should be okay.

47:15.582 --> 47:18.001
Send the police to Heaven and Earth PC
at Dream Mall quickly.

47:18.085 --> 47:19.169
Yes, sir.

47:39.231 --> 47:40.482
Did you find the video?

47:40.566 --> 47:43.235
No, both of them got new phones.

47:44.069 --> 47:46.697
-Did you catch the one who ran?
-Not yet.

47:47.281 --> 47:50.200
Taebaek actually demanded 150 million won
for the settlement.

47:51.159 --> 47:54.913
<i>Your mother said she'd go there</i>
<i>to settle on your behalf.</i>

47:54.997 --> 47:56.206
What time are they meeting?

47:57.791 --> 47:59.126
In 30 minutes.

47:59.209 --> 48:02.546
I'll try my best to drag it out.
Call me when you find the video.

48:03.130 --> 48:05.507
Okay. Please do that for me.

48:13.473 --> 48:14.850
I apologize.

48:15.684 --> 48:17.978
My son's assault is on me.

48:18.520 --> 48:21.106
I'm to blame for not raising him better.

48:21.690 --> 48:25.569
This will never happen again.
Please give him a chance.

48:26.153 --> 48:28.780
How shameless of you
after what he did to those children!

49:02.356 --> 49:04.358
STORED

49:10.197 --> 49:11.531
What the fuck?

49:14.618 --> 49:16.662
I had a hunch, but you actually came here.

49:17.329 --> 49:18.455
Why are you so surprised?

49:18.538 --> 49:20.874
This is where you used to beat me up.

49:20.957 --> 49:23.251
What? Did you rat us out?

49:23.335 --> 49:24.836
It wasn't me.

49:28.924 --> 49:31.426
You wouldn't believe me, though.

49:31.510 --> 49:33.887
How dare you talk back to me?
Do you have a death wish?

49:33.970 --> 49:35.097
Why would I die?

49:36.139 --> 49:37.933
It's your turn to die.

49:39.935 --> 49:41.353
Wow.

49:41.436 --> 49:43.647
I see you're quite fearless
now that I'm alone.

49:43.730 --> 49:46.108
But you're no match for me, f*****.

49:46.191 --> 49:48.860
Yeah, I know you can fight.

49:48.944 --> 49:50.445
But I won't simply take it today.

49:50.529 --> 49:52.447
Then what, motherf*****?

49:54.491 --> 49:56.368
Delete my video right now.

50:00.455 --> 50:01.790
You're after this too?

50:04.000 --> 50:05.001
Amusing.

50:08.839 --> 50:11.591
You wanna act tough
in front of me, fucker?

50:15.470 --> 50:17.180
You son of a bitch.

50:20.517 --> 50:22.018
I wish I could beat you up to a pulp,

50:22.894 --> 50:25.063
but I'll stop here
because I'm quite busy today.

50:29.025 --> 50:30.902
-Give me your phone.
-Get off me.

50:30.986 --> 50:33.321
Get off!

50:33.405 --> 50:34.906
Get off, damn it!

50:36.658 --> 50:38.285
Are you out of your damn mind?

50:41.455 --> 50:44.374
Die!

50:46.835 --> 50:48.211
You damn nutcase.

50:54.551 --> 50:55.844
Give me your phone.

50:57.971 --> 50:59.681
Give me your phone!

51:11.401 --> 51:12.402
Jun-ho!

51:23.872 --> 51:27.167
Get off me. Get the hell off already!

51:28.418 --> 51:30.378
No, you're not going anywhere.

51:31.129 --> 51:32.380
Give me your phone.

51:32.964 --> 51:34.549
Then, I'll forgive you.

51:34.633 --> 51:35.926
Forgive me?

51:36.009 --> 51:37.636
You crazy asshole.

51:37.719 --> 51:41.306
Who do you think you are to forgive me?

51:41.389 --> 51:43.642
I said I'll forgive you!

51:53.026 --> 51:54.444
You little…

52:15.715 --> 52:17.342
I took it away from him.

52:19.719 --> 52:21.638
I didn't do it like them.

52:23.390 --> 52:24.724
I did it my way.

52:29.771 --> 52:31.356
How did I do?

52:34.818 --> 52:35.861
Well done.

52:37.070 --> 52:41.199
You didn't ruin your life for them.

52:43.618 --> 52:44.911
I'm so glad.

52:53.879 --> 52:57.382
TAEBAEK

53:03.597 --> 53:05.015
SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT

53:05.807 --> 53:07.309
TOTAL AMOUNT: 150 MILLION WON

53:16.526 --> 53:17.569
Excuse me.

53:25.201 --> 53:27.078
What do you think you're doing?

53:27.662 --> 53:29.915
Sung Min-jae, Na Ji-hyeok, and Lee Seo-won

53:29.998 --> 53:32.417
were arrested
for aggravated assault, illegal filming

53:32.500 --> 53:34.336
and distribution of illegal content.

53:35.337 --> 53:39.007
They also beat Seo Jun-ho up
on the day of the assault case.

53:39.716 --> 53:42.636
And Lee Seo-won confessed
that Attorney Shin I-rang

53:42.719 --> 53:44.095
only tried to stop them.

53:44.971 --> 53:46.514
What are you talking about?

53:47.307 --> 53:48.558
Hello?

53:48.642 --> 53:49.851
The police?

53:49.935 --> 53:51.061
-Hello?
-Min-jae.

53:51.144 --> 53:52.437
I'll be there immediately.

53:52.520 --> 53:54.314
Did you do something again?

53:57.776 --> 54:00.362
Your son will arrive soon.
Please wait for him downstairs.

54:00.445 --> 54:02.405
Thank you, Ms. Attorney.

54:15.502 --> 54:17.462
Don't you have any words for me?

54:19.297 --> 54:20.632
About what?

54:20.715 --> 54:23.301
I heard you told them
to throw their phones away.

54:23.385 --> 54:24.386
Is it true?

54:26.972 --> 54:28.223
Why are you so surprised?

54:29.057 --> 54:32.268
You resort to any means possible
to win a case.

54:32.352 --> 54:33.687
That's your way, isn't it?

54:39.359 --> 54:40.360
I thought

54:41.027 --> 54:42.654
we were the same kind.

54:46.157 --> 54:47.409
You haven't changed.

54:49.619 --> 54:50.996
Is it because of Shin I-rang?

54:54.416 --> 54:55.750
Is he behind your change?

54:55.834 --> 54:56.876
Mind your own business.

54:56.960 --> 54:59.838
Lee Gang-pung, Kim Su-a, and Jeon Sang-ho.

55:00.797 --> 55:03.091
-They're all dead.
-So what?

55:03.174 --> 55:06.011
All his clients were families
of dead people.

55:07.012 --> 55:09.014
Why does he only take on such cases?

55:09.597 --> 55:11.933
Why does he keep getting involved
with dead people?

55:12.517 --> 55:15.603
Besides, he swore like Lee Gang-pung
and acted like Kim Su-a.

55:15.687 --> 55:18.273
How did he find out
where Jeon Sang-ho's body was buried?

55:18.356 --> 55:19.941
Don't you find it strange at all?

55:25.530 --> 55:26.865
His office

55:28.575 --> 55:30.577
was a shaman's house
until a few months ago.

55:32.037 --> 55:34.622
Shin I-rang can see ghosts.

55:35.290 --> 55:36.708
It's dangerous to be around him.

55:38.585 --> 55:39.794
Stop talking nonsense.

56:19.501 --> 56:20.502
THURSDAY, JUNE 7, 2012

56:20.585 --> 56:22.337
<i>I wonder who's more at fault.</i>

56:22.420 --> 56:24.130
<i>The one who hit them with a brick?</i>

56:24.214 --> 56:26.591
<i>Or the ones who bullied him to death?</i>

56:26.674 --> 56:28.343
<i>He had no choice…</i>

56:28.426 --> 56:29.677
<i>If I become the best attorney,</i>

56:29.761 --> 56:31.012
<i>will I be able to understand him?</i>

56:31.096 --> 56:32.097
<i>If I become the best attorney,</i>

56:32.180 --> 56:36.184
<i>will I be able to speak</i>
<i>for his resentment?</i>

56:38.561 --> 56:40.897
No one was there to understand

56:41.940 --> 56:43.274
why he had to attack them.

56:43.358 --> 56:47.779
<i>Who's there to understand the victim</i>
<i>who had no choice but to attack them?</i>

57:00.291 --> 57:04.129
His office was a shaman's house
until a few months ago.

57:04.212 --> 57:07.340
And my office used to be a shaman's house.

57:33.491 --> 57:35.118
MY DAUGHTER, NA-HYUN

57:36.161 --> 57:37.287
Hi, Na-hyun.

57:37.370 --> 57:40.039
-How have you--
<i>-Have you been to a shaman's house before?</i>

57:41.207 --> 57:42.208
What?

57:42.292 --> 57:45.879
Have you ever visited a shaman
after that incident?

57:46.796 --> 57:49.174
H-How did you…

57:49.257 --> 57:50.967
Was it in Seocho-dong?

57:59.058 --> 58:01.895
I can see and communicate
with dead people.

58:01.978 --> 58:03.605
This time, it was Su-a.

58:03.688 --> 58:06.608
Last time, Lee Gang-pung's spirit told me.

58:10.320 --> 58:11.863
<i>You shouldn't do this to your client!</i>

58:11.946 --> 58:13.615
<i>Are you really the Han Na-hyun I know?</i>

58:13.698 --> 58:16.618
What made you become this inflexible?
You're darn annoying!

58:20.455 --> 58:21.539
So-hyun.

58:22.832 --> 58:24.042
No way.

58:29.422 --> 58:34.260
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

58:36.763 --> 58:38.014
I'm sorry, Mom.

58:38.681 --> 58:41.309
Is Attorney Han aware
that her sister has come?

58:41.893 --> 58:42.894
No.

58:43.520 --> 58:45.146
I don't know what to do.

58:45.730 --> 58:47.357
She'll be shocked if she hears it.

58:48.066 --> 58:50.485
Maybe it's better to keep it from her.

58:53.613 --> 58:55.573
For what she did this time and all,

58:55.657 --> 58:57.575
let's treat her to a meal sometime.

58:58.117 --> 58:59.953
Ask her when she's available.

59:02.705 --> 59:03.706
Okay.

59:23.851 --> 59:25.144
What are you doing here?

59:45.039 --> 59:46.040
Na-hyun.

59:50.962 --> 59:51.963
Attorney Han?

59:52.880 --> 59:54.799
I was meaning to call you.

59:54.882 --> 59:56.301
Do you have time right now?

59:57.510 --> 59:58.761
Why do you ask?

59:58.845 --> 01:00:00.430
I need you to go somewhere with me.

01:00:14.193 --> 01:00:16.154
You want us to ride that?

01:00:17.113 --> 01:00:18.239
You don't want to?

01:00:18.323 --> 01:00:20.783
Well, it's not that I don't want to.

01:00:22.327 --> 01:00:23.453
Good, then.

01:00:24.120 --> 01:00:25.163
I'll go buy tickets.

01:00:30.126 --> 01:00:32.211
I'm afraid of heights.

01:00:36.633 --> 01:00:39.260
You like that?

01:00:39.344 --> 01:00:41.179
I go crazy for them!

01:00:42.722 --> 01:00:44.182
Hold on.

01:00:45.850 --> 01:00:49.395
Does Attorney Han know
that you like roller coasters?

01:00:49.479 --> 01:00:51.981
Of course! We came here
so many times on vacation.

01:00:54.609 --> 01:00:55.652
Then the reason

01:00:56.694 --> 01:00:58.154
she took me here…

01:01:21.928 --> 01:01:23.096
Na-hyun.

01:01:29.268 --> 01:01:32.021
Let's sit in the last row again today.

01:01:32.105 --> 01:01:33.856
-With our hands up.
-With our hands up. Deal?

01:01:53.167 --> 01:01:54.168
Na-hyun.

01:02:51.017 --> 01:02:53.019
<i>-Is it you, So-hyun?</i>
-It's still I-rang.

01:02:53.102 --> 01:02:55.438
Let me be alone with her
without you today.

01:02:55.521 --> 01:02:56.397
<i>Don't you worry.</i>

01:02:56.481 --> 01:02:58.858
I feel so bad for Na-hyun.

01:02:58.941 --> 01:03:00.818
<i>I shouldn't stay here.</i>

01:03:00.902 --> 01:03:02.361
Is it right to pass on like this?

01:03:02.445 --> 01:03:04.781
I don't want to break her heart anymore.

01:03:04.864 --> 01:03:06.824
<i>I see. It was thoughtless of me.</i>

01:03:07.950 --> 01:03:09.160
Where's So-hyun?

01:03:09.243 --> 01:03:10.578
<i>They all passed on.</i>

01:03:10.661 --> 01:03:13.080
<i>-No.</i>
<i>-Take care.</i>

01:03:13.164 --> 01:03:14.415
<i>Don't go.</i>

01:03:14.499 --> 01:03:19.295
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
